---
description: Provider, account, rebuild, resale and local-stack portability
globs:
alwaysApply: true
---

- KlickIt must remain rebuildable, transferable, sellable and provider-replaceable.
- This applies to cloud, AI/MCP, Git, CI, hosting, database, storage, auth, realtime, jobs, communications, monitoring, domain, desktop shell, gateway, OS and hardware assumptions.
- Keep domain/UI code behind internal provider interfaces where practical.
- Use provider-neutral object keys, event contracts and configuration schemas.
- Keep migrations, functions, workflows, build commands and infrastructure configuration in Git.
- Important setup must not exist only in a provider dashboard.
- Cursor and MCP must not be required to build or operate KlickIt.
- Update provider inventory, account transfer and exit documentation whenever a service is added.
- Ask before accepting material lock-in.
- Do not falsely claim that every migration has identical effort.
- Before production, run clean rebuild, database restore, file restore and provider-exit checks.
